# Semantic Commit Messages

Use Conventional Commits format for every commit message:

`type(scope): short imperative summary`

## Allowed Types

- `feat`: new user-facing feature/content
- `fix`: bug fix
- `refactor`: code restructuring without behavior change
- `docs`: documentation-only change
- `chore`: maintenance, config, tooling
- `test`: tests added or updated

## Rules

- Keep subject line concise and imperative.
- Prefer a specific scope (for example: `content`, `seo`, `build`, `workflow`).
- Use body to explain intent/why (1-2 short sentences) when needed.
- Do not add ending punctuation in the subject.

## Examples

- `feat(content): publish two new blog posts for April 2026`
- `fix(seo): correct invalid frontmatter tags in blog posts`
- `chore(workflow): update sync-version automation`
